frameDefinitions: Unless a particular Required_situation obtains, Negative_consequences will follow.
The words in this frame describe an Experiencer's feelings of tolerating with respect to some Content.
The words in this frame have to do with people and the personal Relationships they are or can be a part of.
An Agent behaves as if they were a particular individual or type of Simulated_entity with the intent of misleading observers of their behavior.
An Agent actively (yet not always with success) attempts to keep themselves from participating in an Event.
An Exerter, Action, or Force is capable of exerting or does exert a physical force at a level specified by the target.
frameExamples: You <t>must</t> turn in your test by 5 p.m.
He could not <t>tolerate</t> the smell of coconut .
And of course that drippy <t><fex name='Partner_1'>boyfriend</fex></t> of hers backed her up.
The belfast bank robbers <t>posed</t> as police.
Eugenie loved the sea and was a <t>strong</t> swimmer.
listRoleDefinitions: The state-of-affairs which prevents <fen>Negative_consequences</fen>.
The period during which the <fen>Required_situation</fen> is necessary to prevent negative consequences.
The location within which the <fen>Required_situation</fen> is required.
The <fen>Experiencer</fen> experiences tolerance with respect to the <fen>Content</fen>.

<fen>Content</fen> is what the <fen>Experiencer</fen>'s feeling of tolerance is directed towards..  The <fen>Content</fen> differs from a stimulus because the <fen>Content</fen> is not construed as being direcly responsible for causing the emotion.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is the area about which the <fen>Experiencer</fen> has the  tolerated experience(s).
The <fen>State</fen> is the abstract noun that describes a more lasting experience by the <fen>Experiencer</fen>.
The <fen>Event</fen> is the occasion or happening that <fen>Experiencer</fen>s in a certain emotional state participate in.
The time at which the <fen>Experiencer</fen> is in the state of toleration.
That partner in the <fen>Relationship</fen> who is realized as the subject of verbs in active form sentences, or of adjectives in predicative uses.
That partner in the <fen>Relationship</fen> who is not expressed as the external argument.
The joint construal of both <fen>Partners</fen> in the <fen>Relationship</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person who acts in a misleading way to create the impression that they are a particular individual or type of <fen>Simulated_entity</fen>.
The type or individual that the <fen>Agent</fen> gives the impression of being.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> impersonates the <fen>Simulated_entity</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> gives the impression that they are the <fen>Simulated_entity</fen>.
The Agent who tries to keep an Event from taking place.
The Event is the action or state of affairs that the Agent wishes to prevent.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Agent</fen> prevents the <fen>Event</fen> from taking place.
The <fen>Place </fen> is where the <fen>Agent</fen> attempts to prevent the <fen>Event</fen> from taking place.
The <fen>Exerter</fen> that can or does exert a force of the level specified by the target.
The <fen>Force</fen> that can or does exert a force of the level specified by the target.
The <fen>Action</fen> that can or does exert a force of the level specified by the target.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Exerter</fen>, <fen>Action</fen>, or <fen>Force</fen> can or does exert its force.
The location where the <fen>Exerter</fen>, <fen>Action</fen>, or <fen>Force</fen> can or does exert its force.
listRoleExamples: He was told that <fex>when he got back</fex> , his column needed a serious rethink .
<fex>In California</fex> , seatbelts must be fastened at all times .
Everyone must endure <fex>some disappointments in life</fex>.
They 're very tolerant <fex>about boys' mess in the home and untidiness generally</fex>.
Tracy was in a surprisngly tolerant <fex>mood</fex> today.
<fex>When they are young,</fex>, they  cannot stand extremes of temperature.
Salesmen touted the power <fex>of the engine's motor</fex>.
No one should underestimate the mighty <fex>strength</fex> of the dung beetle.
She gave him a playful, weak <fex>punch</fex> in the arm.
My quads feel particularly weak <fex>after 100 squats</fex>.
Muhammad Ali's force <fex>in the ring</fex> was indisputable.
